spanGrp.span: anin qawasch welwel ed qamayen ed qambng'arqan
I am Welwel of Qamayen, of Qambng'arqan
'mimi ni welwel wa qamayen wa kwa qambng''arqan'
In the old days when I moved to here in Law
qahid aa qanyaseaw hij gwalanyeka aa gwalanyanyand anyagd ba asimjeeg ba law hij a
When I arrived here I met the elders, and the elders of Law that I met were
nilipofika hapo musoma niliwakuta wazee na wazee wa musoma niliowakuta ni
And he was a medicine man
eemeed qamn ab hij gidqobareas qohidanes
But now people here, what is finishing them is
lakini sasa hivi watu hapo kinachowamaliza ni
They have already married into the tribes
gid qamn qut godurmanidew qut asimjeeg abhiji
What is causing many people to fail to speak the language well
kinachowafanya watu wengi kushindwa kuzungumza kinyumbani vizuri
Is that they have married into the other tribes
iisiqen jaft nachand qon gwayam quwar qo nachand
If a child is married into a tribe, they come to change their home to become a member of the tribe
akiolewa mtoto wa kikabila anakuja kubadilisha nyumba kuwa makabila
agwalabe aa emeed gad eyat gwarugw qay abeed
Where does it come from, though, many people are doing the traditions, the elders, the elders of the old days
itokewapi lakini watu kadhaa bado wanafanya mambo ya kinyumbni wazee wazee wa zamani
Those that I met have already died
aa qay balang'nan ng'wakal sen aa gomewa qay gwand
And those of the old days, those who came from Ng'wakala, they died in the old days
'na wa zamani waliotokea ng''wakala nao wameshafariki zamani wapo'
ab gwand ee gwargwed anyasew hij gegur
And there was an elder I met here, he was called
na alikwepo mzee niliyemkuta hapo anaitwa
ga qay balang'nan ng'wakal abeed gwand masanj aa gwand baheba
And in the old days they came from Ng'wakal, there was Masanja and there was Baheeba.
'na zamani walitikea ng''wakal alikwepo masanja na alikwepo na baheba'
I met them then, the family of Mayerba and Geshang'we
gwarugw qay anyasew hij hanang'w su gil aa
The elders I met were these
wazee niyowakuta hapo ni hao na
gwaruk ga mid osh qamn deebug gil aa gwalanyeka
The elders that are here are children who were born there
wazee waliopo ni watoto waliozaliwa huko lakini ni wazee
gadugabalol gid asimjeeg aa qong'ayid deebug ga qamn sijil ha qowu nadeeg saw mad qwayiny ar gid asimjeeg
And those that still speach Asimjeeg, they have become very few and the children who are born no they have already become members of other tribes, they don't understand Asimjeeg
na ambao bado wanazungumza kiasimjeeg wamekuwa wachache na watoto wanaozaliwa sasa hivi wameshakuwa ni makabila wao hawasikii teba kiasimjeega
geagus ijaran aasimjand nal bad asimjand gil geaqus ran gwalanyand qay maj
If you want to meet a traditional Asimjeeg person, maybe follow an elder of the old days who was
ukitaka kumkuta muasimjeega asilia labda umtafute mzee wa zamani aliyekuwa
Who when the elders died he had already grown up
qaremang su qamn ng'etin madgwayiny gid asimjeeg
These youth of today, they don't know Asimjeeg things any more
hawa vijana wa sasa hawajui tena kiasimjeega
They don't know even where we are going
qamn hanang'w asimjeeg ga qay sing'edew hanang'w
Now we Asimjeeg, in the old days we came from
sasa hivi sisi waasimjeega zamani tuliotokea
ga ng'wakal aa gang'edew gayew ha ga qamn du ee
Those who came from Ng'wakala in the east, those are the only ones
'waliotokea ng''wakala ba waliotokea mashariki ndiyo ambao bado tu'
They are the ones who are still trying
ab baloojig ga was baloojigan ab qamn madqang'ad qusugw
For the youth now, they don't know Asimjeeg any more
kwa walio vijana kwa sasa hawajui tena kiasimjeeg
Me, for my history of the old days
In the old days Masaga and
And this medicine man that people would go to
aa gwargwan si mayera aa ginuwasgesh
And this elder named Mayera, together with Ginuwasgeshi
na huyo mzee anayeitwa mayera pamoja na ginuwasgeshi
siid aa orjeed qamat ginuwasgesh aa mayer
Ginuwasgeshi and Mayera is a relative of his
ginuwasgeshi na mayera ni mtu na ndugu yake
And these people have already passed away, his sons remain
na hao wameshafariki wamebaki vijana wake
And now the people we often go to are the sons of Mayera
na sasa tunaowaendeaga ni vijana wa mayera
qamn ha saw sijamew mund ng'anyida
Now they are often depended on
ab hij an bab gad esarman aa madohu qut
And now also we are still dancing, but it's not like then
na hapo pia bado tunachezaga ngoma lakini siyo kivile
genung'wew hanang'w hij qamn sindin ed
And now there's just a place where
ni hapo tu imebaki mahala ambapo bado
In the west there isn't any, Asimjeeg dances have finished
magharibi huko hakuna tena ngoma za kiasimjeega imeisha
